
[1]adverse

   AD'VERSE, a. [L. adversus, opposite; of ad and versus, turned; from
   verto, to turn. See Advert. This word was formerly accented, by some
   authors, on the last syllable; but the accent is now settled on the
   first.]

   1. Opposite; opposing; acting in a contrary direction; conflicting;
   counteracting; as, adverse winds; an adverse party.

   2. Figuratively, opposing desire; contrary to the wishes, or to
   supposed good; hence, unfortunate; calamitous; afflictive; pernicious,
   unprosperous; as, adverse fate or circumstances.
